# npm lockfile and deployment

The installable app lives in **`frontend/`**. All `npm` commands that affect the lockfile must run from **`frontend`** (that folder contains `package.json` and `package-lock.json`).

## When you change dependencies

1. Edit **`frontend/package.json`** (or use `npm install <pkg>` / `npm uninstall <pkg>` from `frontend`).
2. Run **`npm install`** in **`frontend`** so **`frontend/package-lock.json`** updates.
3. Commit **`frontend/package.json`** and **`frontend/package-lock.json`** in the **same** commit.

Never edit `package-lock.json` by hand.

## Verify before push

From `frontend`:

```bash
npm ci
npm run build
```

If `npm ci` fails with a lockfile error, the lockfile is out of date—run `npm install` in `frontend` again and commit the updated lockfile.

## Deploy configuration

Point the host’s **root directory** (or “project folder”) to **`frontend`** if the platform defaults to the repo root—otherwise it will not find the right `package.json` / lockfile pair.
